@startuml Report Generation Flow
title Demo App Flow: Full Report Generation

actor "End-User" as User
participant "Demo App UI\n(AlpineJS)" as UI
participant "ReportBuilderController" as Controller
participant "ReportBuilderRequest\n(Factory)" as Factory
participant "GovernanceManager\n(ALS)" as Governance
participant "DynamicReport (Facade)\nEngine" as Engine
database "Database" as DB

User -> UI : Select Base Model (e.g. 'User')
activate UI
UI -> UI : Initialize AST State

User -> UI : Select Columns & Virtual Attributes
UI -> UI : Update AST (Attributes Array)

User -> UI : Apply Filters
UI -> UI : Update AST (Filters Array)

User -> UI : Click "Generate Report"
UI -> UI : Serialize AST to JSON
UI -> Controller : POST /generate (JSON Payload)
activate Controller

Controller -> Factory : ReportBuilderRequest::createFromPayload(JSON)
activate Factory
Factory --> Controller : Validated AST Request
deactivate Factory

Controller -> Governance : GovernanceManager::getMatrix()
activate Governance
Governance --> Controller : Attribute Restrictions (ALS)
deactivate Governance

Controller -> Engine : DynamicReport::generate(ReportRequest)
activate Engine
Engine -> Engine : extractVirtualAttributeDependencies()
Engine -> Engine : discoverLinks() [bidirectional: forward + reverse]
Engine -> Engine : planJoins() via BFS on bidirectional graph
Engine -> Engine : buildInnerQuery() & applyFilters()
Engine -> DB : Execute Query Builder
activate DB
DB --> Engine : Result Set
deactivate DB
Engine --> Controller : Paginated Data
deactivate Engine

Controller --> UI : JSON Response (Data & Metadata)
deactivate Controller

UI -> UI : Update Data Grid State
UI --> User : Display Generated Report
deactivate UI

@enduml
